Sentencas: Lowering operation temperature of the solid oxide fuel cell is critical to improving its reliability and durability.
Titulo: Enhancement of oxygen reduction reaction through coating a nano-web structured La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3.δ thin-film as a cathode/electrolyte interfacial layer for lowering the operating temperature of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: However, the tradeoff between the operation temperature and the oxygen reduction reaction on the cathode side hinders lowering of the operation temperature.
Titulo: Enhancement of oxygen reduction reaction through coating a nano-web structured La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3.δ thin-film as a cathode/electrolyte interfacial layer for lowering the operating temperature of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: To address this issue, we employ a nano-web-structured La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3.delta (NW-LSCF) thin-film layer as an interlayer on the cathode side.
Titulo: Enhancement of oxygen reduction reaction through coating a nano-web structured La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3.δ thin-film as a cathode/electrolyte interfacial layer for lowering the operating temperature of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: This thin-film layer enables operating the cell at a low temperature with enhancement of the electrochemical performance by increasing the oxygen-reduction reaction site and is fabricated via a simple spin-coating method.
Titulo: Enhancement of oxygen reduction reaction through coating a nano-web structured La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3.δ thin-film as a cathode/electrolyte interfacial layer for lowering the operating temperature of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The large surface area of NW-LSCF enables significant improvement in the oxygen reduction reaction by an increased triple-phase boundary.
Titulo: Enhancement of oxygen reduction reaction through coating a nano-web structured La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3.δ thin-film as a cathode/electrolyte interfacial layer for lowering the operating temperature of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In addition, the adhesion property between the gadolinium-doped ceria electrolyte and cathode is improved by the layer.
Titulo: Enhancement of oxygen reduction reaction through coating a nano-web structured La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3.δ thin-film as a cathode/electrolyte interfacial layer for lowering the operating temperature of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In an anode-support-type single cell test, the peak power density of the cell with NW-LSCF is 0.57 W/cm(2) at 550 degrees C, which is an approximately 63% improvement compared to that of the cell without NW-LSCF.
Titulo: Enhancement of oxygen reduction reaction through coating a nano-web structured La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3.δ thin-film as a cathode/electrolyte interfacial layer for lowering the operating temperature of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Moreover, the value is comparable to the peak power density of the cell without NW-LSCF operating at 600 degrees C.
Titulo: Enhancement of oxygen reduction reaction through coating a nano-web structured La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3.δ thin-film as a cathode/electrolyte interfacial layer for lowering the operating temperature of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: This finding suggests the possibility of lowering the operating temperature of the solid oxide fuel cell by introducing NW-LSCF into the cell.
Titulo: Enhancement of oxygen reduction reaction through coating a nano-web structured La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3.δ thin-film as a cathode/electrolyte interfacial layer for lowering the operating temperature of solid oxide fuel cells
